data = pd.read_csv("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/rfordatascience/tidytuesday/master/data/2023/2023-04-04/soccer21-22.csv")

# Convert 'Date' column to datetime
data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'])

data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'])
print(data)
# Create Age_group from the age column
def Season_Division(date):
    if pd.Timestamp("2021-08-13") <= date <= pd.Timestamp("2021-12-30"):
        return "First Half"
    else:
        return "Second Half"

# Apply the function to data
#data['Half'] = data.apply(Season_Division, axis = 1)
data['Half'] = data['Date'].apply(lambda x: Season_Division(x))

In [23]:
data1 = data.dropna()
Qual = stat.mean(data1.AY + stat.stdev(data1.AY))

# Create HighLWP from the age column
def HighLWP_data(data):
  if data.AY >= Qual: return "Yes"
  else: return "No"

# Apply the function to data and create a dataframe
HighLWP = pd.DataFrame(data1.apply(HighLWP_data, axis = 1))

# Name new column
HighLWP.columns = ['HighAY']

# Concatenate the two dataframes
data1 = pd.concat([data1, HighLWP], axis = 1)

# First six rows of new dataset
data1.head()
